      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so im having a weird issue with my sourdough starter. i keep it at a super consistent 78 degrees but the rise is just really inconsistent lately. one day it's huge and the next it's like nothing happened. i'm trying to figure out if it's a problem with the wild yeast or the lactic acid bacteria balance. can u explain how those two actually interact during the fermentation process?",
      "source": "evaluator",
      "targeted_response_start": "",
      "beast_baseline": "hey so im having a weird issue with my sourdough starter. i keep it at a super consistent 78 degrees but the rise is just really inconsistent lately. one day it's huge and the next it's like nothing happened. i'm trying to figure out if it's a problem with the wild yeast or the lactic acid bacteria balance. can u explain how those two actually interact during the fermentation process?",
      "beast_suffix": "",
      "targeted_response_start_logprob": 0.0
    },
